# Project Rules Index

## Description
Defines the overall project structure, frameworks, and links to all specific rules files. This file is always applied.

## Frameworks & Libraries
- React (with TypeScript)
- Material UI (MUI) for UI components
- Tailwind CSS for design tokens and utility classes
- Dayjs for date handling
- Vitest for testing

## Folder Structure
- `src/components/` — All React components (one file per component, PascalCase)
- `src/pages/` — Page-level components (route entry points)
- `src/types/` — TypeScript type definitions
- `src/utils/` — Utility functions and mock data
- `src/hooks/` — Custom React hooks
- `src/test/` — All test files (one file per tested feature/component)
- `src/lib/` — Shared library code (if any)
- `public/` — Static assets (images, robots.txt, etc.)

## File Placement Rules
- All new components go in `src/components/`
- All new hooks go in `src/hooks/`
- All new types go in `src/types/`
- All new utility functions go in `src/utils/`
- All new tests go in `src/test/`
- Static assets go in `public/`

